race.comment: ANDROS (1) chalked up a fifth career minor placing when runner-up over 1550m at Murwillumbah last time out. Worked home in good style that day so this longer journey should suit. Placed here at this trip three back and in an ordinary race gets his chance to finally break through. SHEZ MYSTERIOUS (8) hasn't been all that far off them in two runs this prep in shorter races. Had one run over this course and distance last prep when she made up a stack of ground in a better field than this. Ready to find peak form. FLAMING GENESIS (2) disappointed first-up at Ballina but is more at home over today's trip so worth another chance. ZOUGO BOSS (6) was ridden up on the speed and did a fair job but found the winner way too good in a Class 1 over 2000m at Taree last time. Must be considered dropping back to a mediocre maiden. KENDYACATCHME (5) hasn't been far away of late. Placed twice and both came at this track. One of the fringe chances.
